      • setColumns

        public void setColumns(List<HiveRegistrationUnit.Column> columns)
        Set the columns for a table or partition.

        Columns does not need to be set for a table if the table's serde already provides the schema, such as Avro tables. Columns does not need to be set for a partition if they are the same as the table's columns.

        Parameters:
        columns -

      • setProp

        public void setProp(String key,
                    Object value)
        Set a table/partition parameter.

        When using HiveMetaStoreBasedRegister, since it internally use Table and Partition which distinguishes between table/partition parameters, storage descriptor parameters, and serde parameters, one may need to distinguish them when constructing a HiveRegistrationUnit by using setProp(String, Object), setStorageProp(String, Object) and setSerDeProp(String, Object). When using query-based Hive registration, they do not need to be distinguished since all parameters will be passed via TBLPROPERTIES.

      • setSerDeProps

        public void setSerDeProps(Path path)
                   throws IOException
        Set serde properties for a table/partition using the table/partition's HiveSerDeManager.

        Requires that the HiveSerDeManager of the table/partition must be specified in Builder#withSerdeManaager(HiveSerDeManager), and the table/partition's location must be specified either in setLocation(String) or via HiveConstants.LOCATION.

        Throws:
        IOException

      • setSerDeProps

        public void setSerDeProps(HiveRegistrationUnit other)
                   throws IOException
        Set serde properties for a table/partition using another table/partition's serde properties.

        A benefit of doing this is to avoid obtaining the schema multiple times when creating a table and a partition with the same schema, or creating several tables and partitions with the same schema. After the first table/partition is created, one can use the same SerDe properties to create the other tables/partitions.

        Throws:
        IOException
